---
title: Parisienne Spiced Prawns with Green beans, Fresh Tomato and Couscous
description: White Peppercorns, Nutmeg, Paprika, Clove Buds, Thyme, Cinnamon, Basil and Bay Leaves are the great eight found in our delicious Parisienne spice mix. It’s fragrant, earthy flavour is a brilliant seasoning for tonight’s ten-minute prawns, which we’re serving alongside stir-fried green beans, fresh tomatoes and fluffy couscous for the perfect quick-fix dinner recipe. Finish off with a squeeze of fresh lemon juice and enjoy!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/parisienne-spiced-prawns-299bc25b-06d8b79a.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/parisienne-spiced-prawns-5c408b8de3f33920667448e2-6f34bf64.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 418 kcal
  fat: 4 g
  saturated fat: 1 g
  carbohydrates: 66 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 25 g
  sodium: 3 g
  serving size: 385
servings: 2
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/parisienne-spiced-prawns-5c408b8de3f33920667448e2
time required: 10 minutes
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: Fusion
---

Trim the @green beans{150%g} then chop into thirds.

Zest and halve the @lemon{1}.

Chop the @tomato{2%medium} into 1cm chunks.

Put the @couscous{150%g} and @vegetable stock powder{1/2%portion} in a #mixing bowl{}.

Pour the boiling @water{300%ml}(for the couscous) into the bowl, stir and cover tightly
with #clingfilm{}. Leave to the side for ~{10%minutes}.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} over medium-high heat.

Add the green beans and stir-fry until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> Add a splash of water every minute or so to help the beans cook and steam.

When the beans are soft enough to eat, add the @king prawns{150%g} and
@Parisienne style herbs{1%portion} to the pan.

Stir-fry for ~{3-4%minutes}, then stir in the @easy garlic{1/2%portion}
and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

> The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Remove from the heat.

Fluff the couscous up with a #fork{}.

Stir in the lemon zest, a glug of @olive oil{} and season to taste with @salt{} and
@black pepper{}.

Mix the chopped tomato through the couscous.

Share the couscous between your bowls.

Season the prawns and beans with salt and pepper.

Squeeze over some lemon juice.

Spoon on top of the couscous. Enjoy!